Retrieve model summary dataframe if it exists.

Source: R/generics.R
glance.Rd

Check if a glance method exits for a given object, either in broom or in broom.mixed. If it does, return the model summary dataframe, if not, return a NULL. In this case, you can try the glance_performance() function.

glance(x, ...)

Arguments

x

model or other R object to convert to single-row data frame
...

other arguments passed to methods
